what has been your biggest loss in life what's your story my biggest loss was the day my grandfather died i feel like no one will ever take his place or even come close to being as wonderful as he was he was a career army man he retired from the us army after serving in the korean conflict and the vietnam war he came home and went back to college at the age of to become a police man for our town he retired from the police department after his second heart attack he was away from home a lot because of the sevice but remained a faithful husband and dedicated father to my mom and her sister he took care of me while my mother single mom worked second shift later he also took care of my cousin while his mom worked he taught us the importance of respecting the american flag and our country he also taught us important things like how to change a flat tire and how to give a firm hand shake my grandfather was a member of the local lions club served on our town developing commitee and was on an inspection commitee for adult care and nursing homes until he was he died in his sleep at his home on jan he was my best friend advisor and a man i am proud to call my pa Avenue Q Wang Mang Pitaten United States Army International Red Cross and Red Crescent Movement Florence Nightingale Family Fancy Crane Fire Emblem: Blazing Sword Care Bears Jon Secada Laura Schlessinger Kimi Finster Taunton, Massachusetts William Westmoreland Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Rugrats The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe Grandview, U.S.A. Cindy Sheehan Ranma __ characters The Inside James I of England Cliff Richard Mid-levels Emperor Guangwu of Han Theodore Roosevelt Futurama (TV series - season 2) Arlington National Cemetery Hollyoaks 2005 trial of Michael Jackson Shaggy dog story Vernon Schillinger Donald Rumsfeld Emperor Wu of Han AFI 100 Years series Kyle Broflovski Douglas MacArthur Tokugawa Ieyasu Vietnam War Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Sin City Platoon (film) Alois Hitler USS Walke 